<description>Having suffered a serious knee injury at the start of the 1999-2000 campaign, Ian made his long-awaited return for West Ham United against Newcastle United at the end of October 2000.
However, he continued to be plagued by niggling injuries that prevented him from fully establishing a place in the line-up.
He netted with a header against Manchester City but then suffered a hamstring injury at Leeds United and concussion led to his absence from the last few games.
A powerful right-sided defender, his height and strength in the tackle were badly missed by the Hammers back line when he was absent.
Ian joined Fulham in January 2004 with a contract  up to June 2007 that was extended to June 2008 in October 2006.

<i>
In addition to the red cards totals shown below, whilst as an unused sub, Ian was sent-off after 73 minutes of Lincoln City's League Two game against Cheltenham Town on 14 November 2009 for violent conduct.</i></description>

